        <description>The U.S. military is maintaining a strong presence in key regions, with increased focus on transport and ISR missions. The USS Tripoli and USS Gerald R. Ford are operating in the U.S. Central Command area of responsibility and Croatia, respectively. These operations suggest ongoing support for regional stability and potential future conflicts.</description>
